  <string name="vehicle_list_hint">
    Touch a vehicle on this screen to be shown more details about that vehicle. Long-touch
    a vehicle to open a context menu of options available for that vehicle.
  </string>

  <string name="main_fuelings_hint_title">Main View</string>
  <string name="main_fuelings_hint">
    This is the main screen, and is probably mostly empty right now. At the top are four rows of
    Averages, which will become meaningful as you add more and more fuelings. Touch a row of
    averages to view more detail about your fuel consumption and costs.\n\nEach of the individual
    fuelings appears in the lower list (which you can scroll up and down.) Touch a fueling to view
    more detail about that fueling, or long-touch a fueling to open a context menu of options.
    \n\nTouch the \"Add\" button in the lower-right to provide fueling information each time you
    fill your vehicle with gas.
  </string>

  <string name="first_vehicle_hint_title">Add or Edit a Vehicle</string>
  <string name="first_vehicle_hint">
    Looks like this is your first time here. Welcome. We hope you find this easy and useful.
    Let\'s start by adding a vehicle. (You can add more Vehicles, later, if you\'d like
    to.)\n\n This screen is where you add or edit vehicles. The only thing you MUST provide is a
    Vehicle Name—or instead of a Vehicle Name, provide a Color, Model and Model Year (in which
    case a Vehicle Name will be created for you). The License Plate and VIN fields are entirely
    optional.
  </string>

  <string name="first_fueling_hint_title">Add or Edit a Fueling</string>
  <string name="first_fueling_hint">
    This screen is where you add (or edit) details when you fill your car with gas. The app
    provides a date and time, but you can change them if you want to. You must provide the
    Distance, Volume, and Total Price Paid.\n\nIf you permit the app to read your
    GPS location, then the Location field will be filled in for you (you are welcome to change
    it if you would like to). The Odometer field is optional—use it if you want to.
  </string>

